tables.table_schema:
CREATE TABLE attendees (
    attendee_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    first_name VARCHAR(255),
    last_name VARCHAR(255),
    email VARCHAR(255),
    company_name VARCHAR(255),
    registration_date TIMESTAMP
)

CREATE TABLE sessions (
    session_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    session_title VARCHAR(100),
    session_time TIMESTAMP,
    room_number INT,
    speaker VARCHAR(100)
);

CREATE TABLE attendee_sessions (
    attendee_id INT,
    session_id INT,
    CONSTRAINT attendee_session_pk PRIMARY KEY (attendee_id, session_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (attendee_id) REFERENCES attendees(attendee_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (session_id) REFERENCES sessions(session_id)
);

CREATE TABLE AttendeeSessions (
	a_id UUID,
	s_id UUID,
	PRIMARY KEY (a_id, s_id),
	FOREIGN KEY (a_id) REFERENCES Attendees(a_id),
	FOREIGN KEY (s_id) REFERENCES Sessions(s_id)
);

CREATE TABLE Schedule (
	schedule_id UUID PRIMARY KEY,
	a_id UUID,
	s_id UUID,
	date DATE,
	FOREIGN KEY (a_id) REFERENCES Attendees(a_id),
	FOREIGN KEY (s_id) REFERENCES Sessions(s_id)
);

CREATE TABLE Attendees (
    attendee_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    first_name VARCHAR(50),
    last_name VARCHAR(50),
    email VARCHAR(100),
    company VARCHAR(100)
);

CREATE TABLE Sessions (
    session_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    session_title VARCHAR(100),
    session_description VARCHAR(250),
    speaker_name VARCHAR(100),
    start_time TIMESTAMP,
    end_time TIMESTAMP
);

CREATE TABLE AttendeeSessions (
    registration_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    attendee_id INT,
    session_id INT,
    registration_date TIMESTAMP,
    FOREIGN KEY (attendee_id) REFERENCES Attendees(attendee_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (session_id) REFERENCES Sessions(session_id)
);

CREATE TABLE RoomSessions (
    room_session_id INT PRIMARY KEY,
    room_id INT,
    session_id INT,
    date DATE,
    start_time TIME,
    end_time TIME,
    FOREIGN KEY (room_id) REFERENCES ConferenceRooms(room_id),
    FOREIGN KEY (session_id) REFERENCES Sessions(session_id)
);
